%define path %{name}-v%{version}
Name: srf
Summary: SRF (Sequence Read Format) is used to store DNA sequence data. 
Version: 0.1
#Serial:
Release: %{revision}.%{distro}
Group: Applications/System
License: Apache License V2.0
Packager: Bret Harry <webmaster@genome.ucla.edu>
URL: http://sourceforge.net/projects/srf/
Source0: http://internap.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/srf/srf-v0.1.tar.gz
#Requires:  
#BuildRequires: 
BuildRoot: %{_tmppath}/%{path}-build

%description
SRF is a generic format for DNA sequence data. The primary motivation for creating SRF has been to enable a single format capable of storing data generated by any DNA sequencing technology. Hence, the format has sufficient flexibility to store data from current and future DNA sequencing technologies at minimal cost of implementation. 

%prep
%setup -n %{name}-%{version}

%build
./configure
make

%install
rm -rf %{buildroot} 
make install DESTDIR=%{buildroot} 

### Addditional files that should be installed.
### Go Here

cd %{buildroot}
find ./ -type f | cut -b2- > %{_tmppath}/%{path}-%{release}-filelist

%files -f %{_tmppath}/%{path}-%{release}-filelist
%defattr(-, root, root)

%clean
rm -rf ${RPM_BUILD_ROOT}

%pre

%post

%preun

%postun

